OL,3,CApple apologises after latest iPad
OL,4,Cadvert sparks backlash
OL,6,FApple has apologised after facing
OL,7,Fbacklash for its new iPad Pro advert,
OL,8,Fwhich shows a huge hydraulic press
OL,9,Fcrushing a collection of instruments
OL,10,Fand art supplies.
OL,12,FIn the video, an industrial-sized
OL,13,Fmetal plate slowly descends,
OL,14,Fdestroying items such as a piano, a
OL,15,Frecord player, cans of paint, books,
OL,16,Fcameras and arcade games.
OL,18,FIt then lifts back up to reveal a
OL,19,Fpristine new iPad Pro, where the
OL,20,Fnarrator announces: "The most powerful
OL,21,FiPad ever is also the thinnest".
